headline: The Top 5 Analyst Questions From Conagra’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: Conagra's second quarter faced notable headwinds, drawing a negative market response as both revenue and adjusted earnings per share came in below Wall Street expectations. Management attributed the underperformance to persistent inflationary pressures, particularly in animal protein inputs and packaging, as well as lingering supply chain constraints that impacted production in core categories like frozen foods and snacks.
